definitions.definition: An eight-day Jewish festival , starting on the 25th day of Kislev , which commemorates the rededication of the temple in Jerusalem after the victory of the Maccabees over the Greek Syrians .

main_definition: ( Judaism ) An eight-day Jewish festival , starting on the 25th day of Kislev , which commemorates the rededication of the temple in Jerusalem after the victory of the Maccabees over the Greek Syrians .
